<p>

Millarde was born in <village wordnetid="108672738" confidence="0.9508927676800064">
<link xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="../615/18522615.xml">
Cincinnati, Ohio</link></village>
, and began his acting in film in 1913 with <link xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="../015/2644015.xml">
Kalem Studios</link> in <village wordnetid="108672738" confidence="0.9508927676800064">
<link xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="../042/645042.xml">
New York City</link></village>
. In 1916, he directed the first of his thirty-two films the most notable of which was <it><link>
If Winter Comes</link></it> for <link>
Fox Film Corporation</link> in 1923 that was based on the <link xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="../186/2351186.xml">
best-selling book in the United States</link> of 1922 by author <physical_entity wordnetid="100001930" confidence="0.8">
<communicator wordnetid="109610660" confidence="0.8">
<person wordnetid="100007846" confidence="0.8">
<causal_agent wordnetid="100007347" confidence="0.8">
