<link xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="../583/2678583.xml">
A.S.M. Hutchinson</link></novelist>
</writer>
</causal_agent>
</person>
</communicator>
</physical_entity>
. Amongst his other directorial works was, 1920's "<it>Over the Hill to the Poorhouse</it>" and the 1922 thriller "<it>My Friend the Devil</it>" based on the <country wordnetid="108544813" confidence="0.9508927676800064">
<link xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="../419/5843419.xml">
French</link></country>
 novel, "<it>Le Docteur Rameau</it>" by <physical_entity wordnetid="100001930" confidence="0.8">
<communicator wordnetid="109610660" confidence="0.8">
<person wordnetid="100007846" confidence="0.8">
<causal_agent wordnetid="100007347" confidence="0.8">
<writer wordnetid="110794014" confidence="0.8">
